    "recap_headline": "Murray State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ST. CHARLES, Mo. -\nEight innings of shutout pitching were not enough for Murray State to come out with the win after a walk-off grand slam from Lindenwood (10-10) gave the Lions the series victory.\nDrew Deremer\nstarted the game for the Racers, tossing the strongest game of his career. He threw 6 1/3 innings of shutout pitching, a career high, while allowing just two hits and striking out two.\nThe Murray State (12-8) offense recorded seven hits but was unable to drive any runs across.\nDaylan Pena\nstarted the second inning with a double down the right-field line, claiming the only Racer extra-base hit of the day.\nConner Cunningham\nwas the only MSU batter to record a multi-hit game, hitting two singles on the day.\nThe Racers will look to bounce back as they return to Murfreesboro to take on Middle Tennessee in the second midweek meeting between the two programs this season.\nFor more information on the Murray State baseball program, visit GoRacers.com and follow @RacersBaseball on Instagram and X."
